SIMPLE: notification
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Notification
<hw>No`ti*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>notification</ets>. See <er>Notify</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of notifying, or giving notice; the act of making known;
especially, the act of giving official notice or information to the
public or to individuals, corporations, companies, or societies, by
words, by writing, or by other means.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Notice given in words or writing, or by
signs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The writing which communicates information; an
advertisement, or citation, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Notify</ent>⟦br⟧
